figgy.title: Title-only ingest of a sound file in figgy will not allow a second save without deleting the first title and replacing it. Javascript may be broken.
Figgy is slow to respond and just errored with "This website is under heavy load (queue full)"

comments.body: This happens when passenger is overloaded with requests, usually from a bunch of manifest requests from DPUL. For it to be happening right now there would have either had to have been a bunch of saves in Figgy at the same time which are in DPUL collections, or a DPUL collection was made or reindexed?
To fix this with infrastructure we'd have to either make more figgy boxes until it can keep up, or add a `figgy3` which just serves manifests, leaving the front-end to other boxes.
